ext-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem=
]">CartDrawer.jsx</code>) keeps state and view tightly coupled =E2=80=94 ea=
sier to reason about solo.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>Why <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-b=
order-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px t=
ext-[0.9rem]">DM Mono</code> + <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0=
.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] p=
x-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Outfit</code>?</strong>
Electronics stores live in a technical space. Monospace for labels/prices/b=
adges signals precision; Outfit for body text keeps it readable. Avoids the=
 generic Inter trap.</p>
